The United States has condemned an attack in Kabul that killed three Americans who were providing healthcare to Afghans. The attack, which targeted civilians at a hospital, is described as despicable and cowardly. The US offers its condolences to the families affected by the attack and expresses continued support for those in Afghanistan who reject violence and strive for a peaceful future. The US is proud of its citizens serving in Afghanistan and working alongside Afghan partners towards a sovereign, stable, secure, and democratic Afghanistan.